{
  "texts": [
    "In the first stage, nonsensical concept identification, the framework pinpoints the specific words in the input statement that contradict commonsense.",
    "For instance, in the statement \"My dad grew volleyballs in his garden,\" the words \"volleyball\" and \"garden\" are identified as nonsensical concepts by TIP.",
    "This is achieved through a nonsensical concept detector, which computes the relative perplexity to assess which words contradict commonsense expectations.",
    "The second stage, knowledge-aware prompting, employs a knowledge generator that dynamically generates relevant implicit knowledge based on the identified nonsensical concepts.",
    "This knowledge is then combined with the nonsensical statement to create an implicit knowledge-augmented prompt."
  ]
}